# multiplat-playlist TODO

## Phase 1: Core Functionality

### CLI Commands
- [ ] Implement `mplay [url]` - Play a single song immediately
- [ ] Implement `mplay queue add [url]` - Add song to queue
- [ ] Implement `mplay queue play` - Start playing the queue
- [ ] Implement `mplay queue list` - Show current queue
- [ ] Implement `mplay queue clear` - Clear the queue
- [ ] Implement `mplay pause` - Pause playback
- [ ] Implement `mplay resume` - Resume playback
- [ ] Implement `mplay next` - Skip to next song
- [ ] Implement `mplay stop` - Stop playback completely
- [ ] Implement `mplay status` - Show current playing song and status
- [ ] Implement `mplay auth` - Spotify OAuth flow

### Spotify Integration
- [ ] Add `github.com/zmb3/spotify` dependency
- [ ] Implement OAuth authentication flow
- [ ] Store and refresh access tokens
- [ ] Fetch track metadata (title, artist, album)
- [ ] Get playback URL for Spotify tracks
- [ ] Handle Spotify API rate limits
- [ ] Handle expired tokens gracefully

### YouTube Integration
- [ ] Verify yt-dlp is installed on system
- [ ] Extract audio stream URL using yt-dlp
- [ ] Fetch video metadata (title, channel)
- [ ] Handle age-restricted videos
- [ ] Handle unavailable videos gracefully
- [ ] Cache stream URLs (they expire after ~6 hours)

### Player Management
- [ ] Verify mpv/ffplay is installed
- [ ] Implement play/pause/stop controls
- [ ] Handle player process lifecycle
- [ ] Track playback state (playing, paused, stopped)
- [ ] Detect when song finishes playing
- [ ] Auto-advance to next song in queue
- [ ] Handle player crashes gracefully

### Queue System
- [ ] Persist queue to disk
- [ ] Load queue on startup
- [ ] Implement queue index tracking
- [ ] Add shuffle functionality
- [ ] Add repeat (one/all) functionality
- [ ] Show queue position and total tracks

